Updates _maxDate to prevent duplicate data collection if user returns to this month view*/Set(_lastDayOfMonth, DateAdd(DateAdd(_firstDayOfMonth, 1, Months), -1, Days));If(_lastDayOfMonth > _maxDate, Set(_maxDate, _lastDayOfMonth); Collect(MyCalendarEvents, Office365.GetEventsCalendarViewV2(_myCalendar.Name, Text(_firstDayOfMonth, UTC), Text(_maxDate, UTC)).value))

/*changes month view to previous month*/Set(_firstDayOfMonth, DateAdd(_firstDayOfMonth, -1, Months));Set(_firstDayInView, DateAdd(_firstDayOfMonth, -(Weekday(_firstDayOfMonth) - 2 + 1), Days));Set(_lastDayOfMonth, DateAdd(DateAdd(_firstDayOfMonth, 1, Months), -1, Days));/*collects calendar events for all days in current month view. Updates _minDate to prevent duplicate data collection if user returns to this month view*/If(_minDate > _firstDayOfMonth, Set(_minDate, _firstDayOfMonth); Collect(MyCalendarEvents, Office365.GetEventsCalendarViewV2(_myCalendar.Name, Text(_minDate, UTC), Text(_lastDayOfMonth, UTC)).value))
